{"title_page": "Benoit Michel", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=August 2013}}\n\n'''Benoit Michel''' (born 1950) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[engineer]].<ref>[http://www.uclouvain.be/benoit.michel UCL University Bio]</ref> He is the author or co-author of more than 20 technical books on [[Microcomputer|microcomputing]], [[Film|cinema]], and [[stereoscopy]].\n\n== Biography ==\nMichel received his degree in civil engineering from [[Universit\u00e9 de Li\u00e8ge]], Belgium, 1976 .<ref name= \"Bio\">[http://www.eyrolles.com/Accueil/Auteur/benoit-michel-97202 Eyrolles Author Bio]</ref>\n\n== Professional history ==\nMichel co-founded \u201cNeurones\u201d, one of the first [[3D Animation|3D cartoon]] [[Animation studio|studios]] in [[Europe]] in 1989. After that, he switched to [[R&D management|R&D project management]] in [[telecommunication]]s, [[human-machine interaction]], [[digital cinema]], and [[multimedia]] and is now at the [[Universit\u00e9 catholique de Louvain|University of Louvain]], successively managing the SIMILAR<ref>[http://www.isca-speech.org/archive_open/specom_04/spc4_627.pdf SIMILAR]</ref> network of excellence on multimodal interfaces, the EDCINE<ref>[http://www.edcine.org/ EDCINE]</ref> project on enhanced digital cinema, the 3D Media research project focusing on [[Stereoscopic image|stereoscopic]] and [[3D imaging]]. He is now working on a medical imaging project called \"InVivo/IGT\"<ref>[http://www.tele.ucl.ac.be/view-project.php?name=In%20ViVo%20IGT InVivo/IGT Project] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120505185905/http://www.tele.ucl.ac.be/view-project.php?name=In%20ViVo%20IGT |date=May 5, 2012 }}</ref> improving the way 3D images are driving [[proton therapy]] machines to cure cancer.\n\nHe is a member of the editorial board of ERCIM News,<ref>[http://www.ercim.eu/news ERCIM News]</ref> and is working as a consultant for the [[European Commission]], the TWIST cluster<ref>[http://twist-cluster.com/cms/en TWIST cluster] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120229045213/http://twist-cluster.com/cms/en |date=February 29, 2012 }}</ref> of [[Wallonia|Walloon]] companies and various private companies and he is the editor of the free \u201cStereoscopyNews\u201d newsletter.<ref>[http://www.stereoscopynews.com StereoscopyNews]</ref> He is co-founder of The European Spaceward Association,<ref>[http://eurospaceward.org/ European Spaceward Association]</ref> a non-profit association with a goal to preserve and improve life on earth by going into space.\n\n== Bibliography ==\n\n* Programmes internes du Commodore PET/CBM (ed B.C.M.)<ref>{{cite book|last=Michel|first=Benoit|title=Programmes internes du Commodore PET/CBM|publisher=B.C.M.|location=Li\u00e8ge, Belgium}}</ref>\n* Le livre du VIC (ed B.C.M.)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=Le livre du VIC|publisher=B.C.M.|location=Li\u00e8ge, Belgium|isbn=978-2-87111-000-2}}</ref>\n* Le livre du 64 (ed B.C.M.)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=Le livre du 64|publisher=B.C.M.|location=Li\u00e8ge, Belgium|isbn=978-2-87111-001-9}}</ref>\n* Le livre de l'AmigaBasic (ed P.S.I.)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=Le livre de l'AmigaBasic|publisher=P.S.I.|location=Paris, France|isbn=978-2-86595-501-5}}</ref>\n* PC, XT, AT: Maintenance et am\u00e9liorations (ed B.C.M.)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=PC, XT, AT: Maintenance et am\u00e9liorations|publisher=B.C.M.|location=Li\u00e8ge, Belgium|isbn=287111014X|last2=Benoit |first2=M.}}</ref>\n* Le livre du Pick (ed B.C.M.)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=Le livre du Pick|publisher=B.C.M.|location=Li\u00e8ge, Belgium|isbn=978-2-87111-013-2|last2=Martin |first2=D.}}</ref>\n* Clefs pour Amiga (ed P.S.I.)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=Clefs pour Amiga|publisher=P.S.I.|location=Paris, France|isbn=978-2-86595-418-6|last2=Labaye |first2=V. |last3=Herzet |first3=G.}}</ref>\n* Personnalisez votre MS-DOS (ed B.C.M.)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=Personnalisez votre MS-DOS|publisher=B.C.M.|location=Li\u00e8ge, Belgium|isbn=978-2-87111-020-0|last2=Surny |first2=A.L.}}</ref>\n* Programmation Windows en Visual BASIC (ed. Dunod Tech, 1992)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=Programmation Windows en Visual BASIC|publisher=Dunod Tech|location=Paris, France}}</ref>\n* Digital cinema : Revolution or Evolution (in 'Film Journal International', Aug 2001)<ref>[https://archive.today/20120707182027/http://business.highbeam.com/3096/article-1G1-77756228/revolution-evolution Digital cinema : Revolution or Evolution]</ref>\n* Similar Dreams 'Multimodal interfaces in our future life' (chapter 8 only) (ed. PUL, 2005)<ref name=Similar>{{cite book|title=Similar Dreams|year=2005|publisher=Presse Universitaires de Louvain|location=Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium|isbn=978-2-930344-91-1|url=http://www.i6doc.com/fr/livre/?GCOI=28001100556070|first=Michel |last=Benoit |last2=Daussogne |first2=S. |last3=Macq |first3=B.|page=143|chapter=\"Chapter 8: SIMILAR work \u201904\"}}</ref>\n* Beyond DCI: The integration of object oriented 3D sound into the Digital Cinema (conference paper presented at NEM Summit 2008)<ref>Beyond DCI: The integration of object oriented 3D sound into the Digital Cinema [http://www.sigma-orionis.com/nem-summit.eu/Presentations/Day3/SessionsB/B7/Beyond_DCI.pdf]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n* 3DTV Le futur de la t\u00e9l\u00e9vision st\u00e9r\u00e9oscopique, avec J-F. Nivart, R. Roberts et V. Breuls de Tiecken, ed. TWIST<ref>[http://www.twist-cluster.com/cms/images/Dossiers/3dtv-ep2.pdf 3DTV Le futur de la t\u00e9l\u00e9vision st\u00e9r\u00e9oscopique]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n* La St\u00e9r\u00e9oscopie Num\u00e9rique (ed Eyrolles, 2011, {{ISBN|978-2-212-129885}})<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=La St\u00e9r\u00e9oscopie Num\u00e9rique|date=November 2011|publisher=Eyrolles|location=Paris, France|isbn=978-2-212-12988-5|pages=291|url=http://www.eyrolles.com/Audiovisuel/Livre/la-stereoscopie-numerique-9782212129885}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Michel, Benoit}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Li\u00e8ge]]\n[[Category:Belgian male writers]]\n[[Category:Belgian technology writers]]\n[[Category:1950 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=August 2013}}\n\n'''Benoit Michel''' (born 1950) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[engineer]].<ref>[http://www.uclouvain.be/benoit.michel UCL University Bio]</ref> He is the author or co-author of more than 20 technical books on [[Microcomputer|microcomputing]], [[Film|cinema]], and [[stereoscopy]].\n\n== Biography ==\nMichel received his degree in civil engineering from [[Universit\u00e9 de Li\u00e8ge]], Belgium, 1976 .<ref name= \"Bio\">[http://www.eyrolles.com/Accueil/Auteur/benoit-michel-97202 Eyrolles Author Bio]</ref>\n\n== Professional history ==\nMichel co-founded \u201cNeurones\u201d, one of the first [[3D Animation|3D cartoon]] [[Animation studio|studios]] in [[Europe]] in 1989. After that, he switched to [[R&D management|R&D project management]] in [[telecommunication]]s, [[human-machine interaction]], [[digital cinema]], and [[multimedia]] and is now at the [[Universit\u00e9 catholique de Louvain|University of Louvain]], successively managing the SIMILAR<ref>[http://www.isca-speech.org/archive_open/specom_04/spc4_627.pdf SIMILAR]</ref> network of excellence on multimodal interfaces, the EDCINE<ref>[http://www.edcine.org/ EDCINE]</ref> project on enhanced digital cinema, the 3D Media research project focusing on [[Stereoscopic image|stereoscopic]] and [[3D imaging]]. He is now working on a medical imaging project called \"InVivo/IGT\"<ref>[http://www.tele.ucl.ac.be/view-project.php?name=In%20ViVo%20IGT InVivo/IGT Project] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120505185905/http://www.tele.ucl.ac.be/view-project.php?name=In%20ViVo%20IGT |date=May 5, 2012 }}</ref> improving the way 3D images are driving [[proton therapy]] machines to cure cancer.\n\nHe is a member of the editorial board of ERCIM News,<ref>[http://www.ercim.eu/news ERCIM News]</ref> and is working as a consultant for the [[European Commission]], the TWIST cluster<ref>[http://twist-cluster.com/cms/en TWIST cluster] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120229045213/http://twist-cluster.com/cms/en |date=February 29, 2012 }}</ref> of [[Wallonia|Walloon]] companies and various private companies and he is the editor of the free \u201cStereoscopyNews\u201d newsletter.<ref>[http://www.stereoscopynews.com StereoscopyNews]</ref> He is co-founder of The European Spaceward Association,<ref>[http://eurospaceward.org/ European Spaceward Association]</ref> a non-profit association with a goal to preserve and improve life on earth by going into space.\n\n== Bibliography ==\n\n* Programmes internes du Commodore PET/CBM (ed B.C.M.)<ref>{{cite book|last=Michel|first=Benoit|title=Programmes internes du Commodore PET/CBM|publisher=B.C.M.|location=Li\u00e8ge, Belgium}}</ref>\n* Le livre du VIC (ed B.C.M.)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=Le livre du VIC|publisher=B.C.M.|location=Li\u00e8ge, Belgium|isbn=978-2-87111-000-2}}</ref>\n* Le livre du 64 (ed B.C.M.)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=Le livre du 64|publisher=B.C.M.|location=Li\u00e8ge, Belgium|isbn=978-2-87111-001-9}}</ref>\n* Le livre de l'AmigaBasic (ed P.S.I.)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=Le livre de l'AmigaBasic|publisher=P.S.I.|location=Paris, France|isbn=978-2-86595-501-5}}</ref>\n* PC, XT, AT: Maintenance et am\u00e9liorations (ed B.C.M.)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=PC, XT, AT: Maintenance et am\u00e9liorations|publisher=B.C.M.|location=Li\u00e8ge, Belgium|isbn=287111014X|last2=Benoit |first2=M.}}</ref>\n* Le livre du Pick (ed B.C.M.)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=Le livre du Pick|publisher=B.C.M.|location=Li\u00e8ge, Belgium|isbn=978-2-87111-013-2|last2=Martin |first2=D.}}</ref>\n* Clefs pour Amiga (ed P.S.I.)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=Clefs pour Amiga|publisher=P.S.I.|location=Paris, France|isbn=978-2-86595-418-6|last2=Labaye |first2=V. |last3=Herzet |first3=G.}}</ref>\n* Personnalisez votre MS-DOS (ed B.C.M.)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=Personnalisez votre MS-DOS|publisher=B.C.M.|location=Li\u00e8ge, Belgium|isbn=978-2-87111-020-0|last2=Surny |first2=A.L.}}</ref>\n* Programmation Windows en Visual BASIC (ed. Dunod Tech, 1992)<ref>{{cite book|first=Michel|last=Benoit|title=Programmation Windows en Visual BASIC|publisher=Dunod Tech|location=Paris, France}}</ref>\n* Digital cinema : Revolution or Evolution (in 'Film Journal International', Aug 2001)<ref>[https://archive.today/20120707182027/http://business.highbeam.com/3096/article-1G1-77756228/revolution-evolution Digital cinema : Revolution or Evolution]</ref>\n* Similar Dreams 'Multimodal interfaces in our future life' (chapter 8 only) (ed. PUL, 2005)<ref name=Similar>{{cite book|title=Similar Dreams|year=2005|publisher=Presse Universitaires de Louvain|location=Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium|isbn=978-2-930344-91-1|url=http://www.i6doc.com/fr/livre/?GCOI=28001100556070|first=Michel |last=Benoit |last2=Daussogne |first2=S. |last3=Macq |first3=B.|page=143|chapter=\"Chapter 8: SIMILAR work \u201904\"}}</ref>\n* Beyond DCI: The integration of object oriented 3D sound into the Digital Cinema (conference paper presented at NEM Summit 2008)<ref>Beyond DCI: The integration of object oriented 3D sound into the Digital Cinema [http://www.sigma-orionis.com/nem-summit.eu/Presentations/Day3/SessionsB/B7/Beyond_DCI.pdf]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n* 3DTV Le futur de la t\u00e9l\u00e9vision st\u00e9r\u00e9oscopique, avec J-F. Nivart, R. Roberts et V. Breuls de Tiecken, ed. TWIST<ref>[http://www.twist-cluster.com